.TH 1985 1 "June 2026" "1985 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
1985 \- Amstrad PCW 8256 emulator
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B 1985
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B 1985
is an Amstrad PCW 8256 emulator written in C with SDL3. Sibling project
to 1984 (the Amstrad CPC emulator) sharing build system, F9 overlay,
and Z80 core. The PCW family ran CP/M Plus on a Z80 with a Motorola
6845 CRTC, a 720x256 monochrome green-phosphor display, an NEC uPD765A
floppy controller, and 256 KB of banked RAM.
.PP
On first run
.B 1985
creates
.IR ~/.config/1985/1985.conf
with sensible defaults; edit it directly or use the F9 overlay.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --config= PATH
Read configuration from
.I PATH
instead of
.IR ~/.config/1985/1985.conf .
.TP
.BI --memory= KB
RAM size in kilobytes: 256, 512 or 2048 (overrides config).
.TP
.BI --disk-a= PATH
Mount a .dsk image in drive A.
.TP
.BI --disk-b= PATH
Mount a .dsk image in drive B.
.TP
.BI --paste= TEXT
Type TEXT verbatim after boot.
.TP
.BI --load-sna= PATH
Load a .sna snapshot at init (stubbed).
.TP
.BI --save-sna-at= N:PATH
Save .sna at frame N (stubbed).
.TP
.BI --screenshot-at= N:PATH
Save a PPM screenshot at frame N and exit.
.TP
.BI --gif-out= PATH
Record GIF from boot to PATH (pair with --exit-after).
.TP
.BI --exit-after= N
Quit after frame N.
.TP
.B --monitor-pty
Open a PTY for the F8 memory monitor.
.TP
.B --kbd-pty
Open a PTY that injects writes as keystrokes.
.TP
.BI --symbols= PATH
Load an SDCC .map for the F8 disassembler.
.TP
.BR -h ", " --help
Show help and exit.
.SH KEYBOARD SHORTCUTS
.TP
.B Click in window
Capture keyboard input for the guest.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Enter
Release captured keyboard input.
.TP
.B F4
Save .ppm screenshot.
.TP
.B F5
Warm reset.
.TP
.B F8
Open / close memory monitor.
.TP
.B F9
Open options overlay.
.TP
.B F11
Toggle fullscreen.
.TP
.B F12
Quit.
.TP
.B Ctrl+V
Paste clipboard.
.SH OVERLAY
Four tabs:
.B General
(model, RAM, debug toggle),
.B Media
(drive A / B file pickers),
.B Extensions
(PDF printer folder, second drive, backplane, serial, PerryFi,
DK'tronics sound/joystick),
.B Advanced
(smoothing, monochrome tint, FPS, trace toggles, snapshot load/save).
The Advanced tab is hidden unless
.B tinker=true
is set in the config.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/1985/1985.conf
Configuration file.
